Retail Sales EDA Analysis – Portfolio Project

Problem / Goal: Identify profitability gaps across product categories and provide actionable insights, focusing on Furniture.

Actions Taken:

Cleaned and standardized dataset, fixed date formats.

Calculated KPIs and profit margins by category and sub-category.

Created clear visualizations for executive insights.

Key Results:

Furniture underperforming: Tables (-$17,725), Bookcases (-$3,472).

Technology and Office Supplies are strongest categories.

Recommendations: optimize production costs, pricing, discounts, and product portfolio to improve margins.

Tools Used: Excel, Python (pandas, matplotlib), data visualization.

Outcome: Ready-to-use executive insights with charts and actionable recommendations for decision-making.
